    <string name="api_text_launcher"><![CDATA[<strong>Launcher Control</strong>
<br>
<br>
Show/hide launcher:
<br>
In MacroDroid: Actions -> Send Intent
<br>
<strong>Target</strong>: Broadcast<br>
<strong>Action:</strong> com.salat.gbinder.TOGGLE_LAUNCHER<br>
<strong>Package</strong>: com.salat.gbinder
]]></string>
    <string name="api_text"><![CDATA[<strong>Receiving Key Press Events</strong>
<br>
In MacroDroid: Triggers -> Intent Received
<br>
<br>
<strong>Actions</strong>:
<br>\"com.salat.gbinder.SHORT_CLICK\"
<br>\"com.salat.gbinder.LONG_PRESS\"
<br>\"com.salat.gbinder.MULTI_LONG_PRESS\"
<br>\"com.salat.gbinder.DOUBLE_CLICK\"
<br>\"com.salat.gbinder.HOLD_START\"
<br>\"com.salat.gbinder.HOLD_STOP\"
<br>\"com.salat.gbinder.KEY_EVENT\"
<br>
<br>
<strong>Additional</strong>:
<br>\"code\" -> keyCode of the key.
<br>for KEY_EVENT additionally: \"event\" -> [0|1|3] where 0 = DOWN, 1 = UP, 3 = CANCEL <br>and \"func\" -> system function code
<br>
<br>for MULTI_LONG_PRESS, the \"code\" parameter is received in the format -> 119+200087 with key codes, the code is formed from the smaller number to the larger
]]></string>
    <string name="api_text2"><![CDATA[<strong>Working with Audio Sources</strong>
<br>
<br>
To listen for changes in audio sources on the head unit:
<br>
In MacroDroid: Triggers -> Intent Received
<br>
<strong>Action</strong>: com.salat.gbinder.AUDIO_SOURCE_CHANGED<br>
<strong>Additional</strong>: source=[USB|BT|RADIO|CPAA|ONLINE|OTHER|YUNTING|UNKNOWN]
<br>
<br>
To change the current audio source of the head unit:
<br>
In MacroDroid: Actions -> Send Intent
<br>
<strong>Target</strong>: Broadcast<br>
<strong>Action</strong>: com.salat.gbinder.SET_AUDIO_SOURCE<br>
<strong>Package</strong>: com.salat.gbinder<br>
<strong>Additional 1</strong>: target=[USB|BT|RADIO|CPAA|ONLINE|OTHER|YUNTING|UNKNOWN]<br>
<strong>Additional 2</strong>: optional source=[UNKNOWN|WECARFLOW|KUWO|KUGOU|NETEASE_CLOUD|SOHU|JINRI|QYS|OTHER|FANDENG|TENCENT_VIDEO|XMLY|GC|HUOSHAN|BILIBILI|THUNDER_VOICE|CMVIDEO_VOICE]<br>
<strong>Additional 3</strong>: optional autoplay=[1|0]
]]></string>
    <string name="api_text3"><![CDATA[<strong>Media Control</strong>
<br>
<br>
Enabling and disabling media control:
<br>
In MacroDroid: Actions -> Send Intent
<br>
<strong>Target</strong>: Broadcast<br><br>
<strong>Action:</strong> com.salat.gbinder.TEMPORARY_DISABLE_MEDIA_CONTROL<br>
<strong>Additional:</strong> duration -> Duration of disabling in seconds<br><br>
<strong>Other actions:</strong>
<br>com.salat.gbinder.ENABLE_MEDIA_CONTROL
<br>com.salat.gbinder.SMART_ENABLE_MEDIA_CONTROL
<br>com.salat.gbinder.DISABLE_MEDIA_CONTROL<br><br>
<strong>Package</strong>: com.salat.gbinder<br>
"SMART" - Enables only if it was previously enabled manually
]]></string>
    <string name="api_text4"><![CDATA[<strong>Receiving Active Media Session Data</strong>
<br>
<br>
Playback status information:<br>
<strong>Action:</strong> com.salat.gbinder.PLAYBACK_STATE<br>
<strong>Additional:</strong> isPlaying=[0|1] -> 1 playback is active, 0 nothing is playing
<br>
<br>
Current track data:<br>
<strong>Action:</strong> com.salat.gbinder.PLAYBACK_METADATA
<br><strong>Additional 1:</strong> id -> unique track identifier
<br><strong>Additional 2:</strong> packageName -> package name of the app playing the media session
<br><strong>Additional 3:</strong> appName -> application name
<br><strong>Additional 4:</strong> title -> title
<br><strong>Additional 5:</strong> artist -> artist
<br><strong>Additional 6:</strong> album -> album name
<br><strong>Additional 7:</strong> uri -> track URI
<br><strong>Additional 8:</strong> coverUri -> cover art URI
<br>
<br>
Intents are sent only when media data changes; you can manually request them via an outgoing broadcast:<br>
<strong>Action:</strong> com.salat.gbinder.REQUEST_PLAYBACK_INFO
]]></string>
    <string name="api_text5"><![CDATA[<strong>Working with Phone Calls</strong>
<br>
<br>
In MacroDroid: Actions -> Send Intent
<br>
<br>
Make a phone call<br>
<strong>Action 1:</strong> com.salat.gbinder.PHONE_CALL
<br><strong>Additional:</strong> number -> phone number (specify the variable type as "string", otherwise the "+" in the number will be lost)
<br>
<br>
Answer a call<br>
<strong>Action 2:</strong> com.salat.gbinder.ANSWER_CALL
<br>
<br>
Reject a call<br>
<strong>Action 3:</strong> com.salat.gbinder.REJECT_CALL
<br>
<br>
Disconnect a call<br>
<strong>Action 5:</strong> com.salat.gbinder.DISCONNECT_CALL
]]></string>
    <string name="api_text6"><![CDATA[<strong>Camera Control</strong>
<br>
<br>
Show/hide 360 cameras:
<br>
In MacroDroid: Actions -> Send Intent
<br>
<strong>Target</strong>: Broadcast<br>
<strong>Actions:</strong>
<br>com.salat.gbinder.TOGGLE_CAMERA<br>
<strong>Package</strong>: com.salat.gbinder
]]></string>
    <string name="api_text7"><![CDATA[<strong>Setting Configurator Value</strong>
<br>
<br>
In MacroDroid: Actions -> Send Intent
<br>
<strong>Target</strong>: Broadcast<br>
<strong>Action1:</strong> com.salat.gbinder.SET_INT_PROPERTY<br>
<strong>Action2:</strong> com.salat.gbinder.SET_FLOAT_PROPERTY<br>
<strong>Package</strong>: com.salat.gbinder<br><br>
<strong>Additional1:</strong> id -> parameter identifier<br>
<strong>Additional2:</strong> value -> new value<br>
<strong>Additional3:</strong> area -> scope of application (optional)
]]></string>
    <string name="api_text8"><![CDATA[<strong>Retrieving Values and Subscribing to Value Changes</strong>
<br>
<br>
In MacroDroid: Actions -> Send Intent
<br>
<strong>Target</strong>: Broadcast<br>
<strong>Action1:</strong> com.salat.gbinder.GET_INT_PROPERTY<br>
<strong>Action2:</strong> com.salat.gbinder.GET_FLOAT_PROPERTY<br>
<strong>Action3:</strong> com.salat.gbinder.LISTEN_PROPERTY_CHANGES<br> - subscribe once, and then an action will be received for each change of the specified function
<strong>Package</strong>: com.salat.gbinder<br><br>
<strong>Additional1:</strong> id -> parameter identifier<br>
<strong>Additional2:</strong> area -> scope of application (optional)
<br><br>
In response to GET_*, the action com.salat.gbinder.PROPERTY_VALUE_RESULT is received<br>
In response to LISTEN_*, the action com.salat.gbinder.PROPERTY_VALUE_CHANGED is received<br>
<strong>Additional1</strong>: id = function identifier<br>
<strong>Additional2</strong>: area = scope of application<br>
<strong>Additional3</strong>: value = current value
]]></string>
    <string name="api_text9"><![CDATA[<strong>Retrieving Sensor Values and Subscribing to Sensor Value Changes</strong>
<br>
<br>
In MacroDroid: Actions -> Send Intent
<br>
<strong>Target</strong>: Broadcast<br>
<strong>Package</strong>: com.salat.gbinder<br><br>
<strong>Action1:</strong> com.salat.gbinder.GET_INT_SENSOR<br>
<strong>Action2:</strong> com.salat.gbinder.GET_FLOAT_SENSOR<br>
<strong>Action3:</strong> com.salat.gbinder.LISTEN_SENSOR_CHANGES<br>
 - subscribe once, and then an action will be received for each sensor change. Not all sensors are supported; functionality is determined experimentally.<br>
<strong>Additional:</strong> id -> parameter identifier<br><br>
In response to GET_*_SENSOR, the action com.salat.gbinder.SENSOR_*_RESULT is received<br>
In response to LISTEN_SENSOR_*, the action com.salat.gbinder.SENSOR_VALUE_CHANGED (for FLOAT values)<br>
and com.salat.gbinder.SENSOR_*_CHANGED is received<br>
<strong>Additional1</strong>: id = sensor identifier<br>
<strong>Additional2</strong>: value = current value
]]></string>
    <string name="api_text10"><![CDATA[<strong>Retrieving Info Parameter Values</strong>
<br>
<br>
In MacroDroid: Actions -> Send Intent
<br>
<strong>Target</strong>: Broadcast<br>
<strong>Package</strong>: com.salat.gbinder<br><br>
<strong>Action1:</strong> com.salat.gbinder.GET_INT_INFO<br>
<strong>Action2:</strong> com.salat.gbinder.GET_FLOAT_INFO<br>
<strong>Action3:</strong> com.salat.gbinder.GET_STRING_INFO<br><br>
In response to GET_*_INFO, the action com.salat.gbinder.INFO_VALUE_RESULT is received<br>
<strong>Additional1</strong>: id = parameter identifier<br>
<strong>Additional2</strong>: value = current value
]]></string>
